                    <head><hi rend="italic">Executive Order No. 8702, Signed by President Roosevelt,
                            March 4, 1941</hi><note n="51" type="source" xml:id="d174fn51">Reprinted
                            from Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 8, 1941
                            (vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, No. 89), p. 246.</note></head>
                    <p>Pursuant to the authority vested in me by the provisions of section 6 of the
                        act of Congress approved July 2, 1940, entitled “<hi rend="smallcaps">An Act
                            To</hi> expedite the strengthening of the national defense”, I hereby
                        prescribe the following additional regulations governing the exportation of
                        the articles and materials named in my proclamation of March 4, 1941:</p>
